.TH HSH 1 "january 2024" "v1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- a simple Unix command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a simple Unix shell written in C.
It allows users to execute commands entered by the user or read from standard
input. The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

The shell supports execution of commands using absolute paths, relative paths,
and PATH environment variable resolution.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.EX
$ ./hsh
($) ls
main.c shell.h helpers.c
($) exit
.EE

Non-interactive mode:
.EX
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
main.c shell.h helpers.c
.EE

.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are supported:

.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.TP
.B env
Print the current environment.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell exits with status 0 on success.
If an error occurs, a non-zero value is returned.

